Heat the olive oil in a large pan and saut√© the onions, fennel, diced chorizo, chilli, ground fennel seeds and  garlic for a few minutes.Add the paprika, thyme, saffron, bay leaves and tomatoes and cook until reduced to a thickish sauce.Add the fish stock (or water) and white wine and bring to a simmer.Add the cooked mussels and cook until they are all open. Discard any that have not opened.Put the fish pieces into the stew and stir in the almonds.Heat for a minute or two and serve with seasonal greens, steamed potatoes and wedges of lemon.